The paper deals with the study of the structure of solutions for random k-SAT and random CSPs, which are problems in computational complexity theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also introduces a new concept to characterize the similarity between solutions, which could fall under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The study of phase transitions and singular points in the limit of average similarity degree could also be related to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
